60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Avoiding blows unconcious better than I did when I was on my</span><hr size=1> I was in east commonlands last night working on my recently acquired backstab skill (You Backstab an Orc Pawn for 30 damage!) when I heard cries for help come from the nearby orc camp. <BR> As I came over the hill I saw a young dark elf shadowknight and a rogue surrounded by 2 orc centurions and a Young Kodiak. <BR> I rushed down the hill readying my Crookstinger as I made a beeline for the back of the YK. <BR>  <BR> My backstab did not hit for full damage but the dagger effect went off and poison began to steal the bears life away. As the bear turned on me I was able to coax the dagger into poisoning one of the orcs, then turned my attention to the bear switching to my dragoon dirk to end is life quickly. <BR>  <BR> As the Young kodiak bear dropped to the ground, the young shadowknight fell to the crushing blows of the two orcs still alive. Badly wounded but convinced I could win the fight with the other rogue still fighting with me, I pressed the battle on. <BR>  <BR> The poisoned orc fell as I my health dropped very low, compromising my agility. Somewhat delirious from my injuries I tried to finish the remaining centurion that was much stronger than the other. <BR>  <BR> And then my worst fears came true: <BR> You try to pierce and Orc Centurion but MISS! <BR> You try to pierce and Orc Centurion but MISS! <BR> You try to pierce and Orc Centurion but MISS! <BR> and so on.... I suddenly could not hit the vile orc and he began to not miss any of his blows. <BR>  <BR> A high elven finger-waggler watched intently as the battle swayed against us... offering no assistance - and then I went unconcious... <BR>  <BR> The other rogue fought on as the Centurion Tried to crush my nearly lifeless body into the soft grass of the commonlands. <BR> But the Orc could not hit me... I held my last dying breath as I counted each of his swings at my body, waiting for darkness to come over me... <BR>  <BR> After missing 10 swings at my almost dead body - the young rogue trying her best to kill the orc with her spear was able to do so as I regained conciousness. <BR>  <BR> I have never in all my days had such a close brush with death as that - to have a creature unable to do a mere 5 points of damage to end your life and not hit once in so many tries... <BR>  <BR> My thanks to the young dark elven rogue melia of the 8th circle - it was an honor to fight by your side and my eternal thanks for saving my life. <BR>  <p><br>
Noelle<br>
10th Circle Dark Elf Rogue<br>
Xegony<br>
